Summary: This section discusses the concept of "smoke and mirrors" in game development, where developers can create the illusion of complexity and excitement without necessarily implementing it fully.

Key Rule: In game development, developers can create the illusion of a more complex, interactive, and graphically exciting world than what is actually implemented, a technique referred to as "smoke and mirrors."
